{{Infobox University |name = St. Augustine International University (SAIU) |image = |motto = |established = 2011 |type = Private |chancellor = [[Tress Bucyanayandi]] |vice_chancellor = [[Charity Basaza Mulenga]] |city = [[Kampala]] |country = [[Uganda]] |students = |staff = |campus = Urban |website = [http://www.saiu.ac.ug/ Homepage] }}
'''St. Augustine International University''' (SAIU) is a [[university]] in [[Uganda]].
==Location== SAIU is a multi-campus university. It maintains the following campuses:<ref>{{cite web|title=The Campuses of St. Augustine International University|accessdate=9 July 2014|first=.|last=SAIU|url=http://www.saiu.ac.ug/prospects/campuses.php|publisher=St. Augustine International University (SAIU)|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140528160417/http://saiu.ac.ug/prospects/campuses.php|archivedate=28 May 2014|df=}}</ref> ;Bunga Campus The main campus is located in the neighborhood of ''Bunga'', in [[Makindye Division]], one of the five administrative divisions of Uganda's capital city, [[Kampala]]. This location lies approximately {{convert|8|km|mi}}, by road, southeast of the city's [[central business district]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=9 July 2014| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Uganda_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Gaba%20(Western%20Province)&toplace=Kampala%20()&fromlat=0.2647222&tolat=0.3155556&fromlng=32.6272222&tolng=32.5655556|title= Map Showing Central Kampala And Bunga With Distance Indicator| publisher=Globefeed.com}}</ref> The approximate coordinates of the main campus of St. Augustine International University are:0°16'21.0"N, 32°37'19.0"E (Latitude:0.272500; Longitude:32.621944).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/0%C2%B016'21.0%22N+32%C2%B037'19.0%22E/@0.2731811,32.6212782,17z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x0|first=.|last=Google|publisher=[[Google|Google Maps]]|accessdate=9 July 2014|title=Location of Main Campus of St. Augustine International University At Google Maps}}</ref> ;Kisoro Campus The Kisoro campus is located in the southwestern Ugandan town of [[Kisoro]], approximately {{convert|465|km|mi}}, by road, southwest of Kampala.<ref>{{cite web|title=Distance Between Kampala And Kisoro With Map|accessdate=9 July 2014|publisher=Globefeed.com| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Uganda_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Kisoro%20(Kisoro)%20&toplace=Kampala%20()%20&fromlat=-1.3538889&tolat=0.3155556&fromlng=29.6983333&tolng=32.5655556}}</ref> The campus is close to [[Mutolere Hospital|Saint Francis Hospital Mutolere]], which will serve as one of the teaching hospitals of the university. ;Mulago Campus The Mulago campus is located on [[Mulago|Mulago Hill]], in [[Kawempe Division]], in northern Kampala, approximately {{convert|5|km|mi}}, by road, north of the city's [[central business district]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=9 July 2014|publisher=Globefeed.com| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Uganda_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Mulago%20(Western%20Province)&toplace=Kampala%20()&fromlat=0.35&tolat=0.3155556&fromlng=32.5833333&tolng=32.5655556| title=Distance Between Central Kampala And Mulago With Map}}</ref> This location is adjacent to [[Mulago Hospital|Mulago National Referral Hospital]], another teaching hospital of the university. ;Namugongo Campus The Namugongo campus is located at [[Namugongo]], [[Kira Town]], [[Wakiso District]], approximately {{convert|15|km|mi}}, by road, northeast of downtown Kampala.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=9 July 2014|publisher=Globefeed.com|url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Uganda_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Namugongo%20(Western%20Province)&toplace=Kampala%20()%20&fromlat=0.3825&tolat=0.3155556&fromlng=32.6463889&tolng=32.5655556|title=Map Showing Central Kampala And Namugongo With Distance Indicator}}</ref> The location lies close to the shrines of the [[Uganda Martyrs]], with streams flowing through the campus. The College of Agriculture and Veterinary Medicine will be based here.
==Overview== SAIU is a private university in Uganda, established in 2011. It is accredited by the Uganda National Council for Higher Education, the national body that licenses institutions of higher education in the country.<ref>{{cite web | last=UNCHE | url=http://www.unche.or.ug/institutions/private-universities/page/3|title=Uganda National Council for Higher Education: Private Universities | accessdate=9 July 2014 | publisher=Uganda National Council for Higher Education (UNCHE)}}</ref> The multi-campus university is one of a number of private universities accredited between 2010 and 2014.<ref>{{cite web | title=Uganda Registers New Private University | newspaper=[[New Vision]] (Kampala) | date=25 March 2013 | accessdate=9 July 2014 | url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/641000-uganda-registers-new-private-university.html | last=Conan Businge | first=and Gloria Nakajubi}}</ref> The founding vice chancellor of the university is [[Charity Basaza Mulenga]], an electrical and computer science engineer trained at [[Makerere University]] in Uganda and [[Loughborough University]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.saiu.ac.ug/documents/saiu-prospectus-2013.pdf | title=St. Augustine International University Prospectus | publisher=St. Augustine International University (SAIU) | last=SAIU | accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref>
