{{Infobox journal | title = The Reading Teacher | cover = The_Reading_Teacher_cover.gif | discipline = [[Education]] | abbreviation = Read. Teach. | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[International Literacy Association]] | country = | frequency = 6/year | history = 1947-present | openaccess = | impact = 0.770 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1002/(ISSN)1936-2714 | link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1002/(ISSN)1936-2714/currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1002/(ISSN)1936-2714/issues | link2-name = Online archive | editors = Jan Lacina, Robin Griffith | CODEN = REDTAH | LCCN = 58026936 | OCLC = 01681346 | ISSN = 0034-0561 | eISSN = 1936-2714 }} '''''The Reading Teacher''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published six times per year by [[Wiley-Blackwell]]. The current editors are Jan Lacina ([[Texas Christian University]]) and Robin Griffith ([[Texas Christian University]]). ''The Reading Teacher'' is one of three journals published on behalf of the [[International Literacy Association]]. It covers practical teaching ideas, research, and professional development for teachers of children up to age 12.
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 0.770, ranking it 93rd out of 203 journals in the category "Education & Educational Research".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2012 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Education & Educational Research |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2012-08-18 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
