{{Infobox organization | name = Vancouver Community Network | logo = [[File:VCN-logo.png|VCN-logo|200px|Image: 200 pixels]] | map = {{Coord|49|16|56.59|N|123|6|26.87|W}} | formation = {{start date and age|1993|05|21}} | founder = Brian Campbell | founding_location = Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada | type = Non-profit | location = Woodward's Heritage Building, Suite 280-111, West Hastings, Vancouver, BC | services = Free Community IT Services | website = https://www2.vcn.bc.ca/ }}
'''Vancouver Community Network''' (or '''VCN''') is a community-owned provider of internet tools and services in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] for sharing the broadest range of information, experience, ideas, and wisdom. It was originally the Vancouver Regional FreeNet, which offered text-based access to community information and to the Internet. It continues to provides free internet services for individuals and non-profit groups, including dial-up, tech support and web hosting.
